mod BinaryComprehension
  ###
  Binary comprehension generators (v0.22.0).

  `for <<byte <- source>>` iterates the bytes of a `Bitstring`
  source and yields each byte to the comprehension body. Segment
  specifiers work the same as in binary patterns, so
  `for <<word::16 <- buf>>` iterates 16-bit words; `for <<ch::utf8
  <- text>>` iterates UTF-8 code points.
  ###

  ## Enumerate every byte of a three-byte binary into a list.
  fn bytes_of(buf: Bitstring) -> List(Int) =
    [b for <<b <- buf>>]

  ## Sum the bytes of a binary by running the comprehension into a fold.
  fn byte_sum(buf: Bitstring) -> Int =
    Std.List.foldl([b for <<b <- buf>>], 0, fn(b) -> fn(acc) -> acc + b)

  ## Entry point used by `mix cure.check.examples`.
  fn main() -> Int =
    byte_sum(<<1, 2, 3, 4>>)
